# Next.js App Router Structure

This project uses Next.js App Router for page routing and organization. The main entry point is [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx).

## Key Routes

- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Homepage
- [src/app/blog](mdc:src/app/blog) - Blog section
- [src/app/toolbox](mdc:src/app/toolbox) - Toolbox section
- [src/app/category](mdc:src/app/category) - Category pages
- [src/app/topics](mdc:src/app/topics) - Topics section
- [src/app/api](mdc:src/app/api) - API routes

## Routing Conventions

1. Each route should have its own directory in the `src/app` folder
2. Use `page.tsx` for the main page component of each route
3. Use `layout.tsx` for route-specific layouts
4. Dynamic routes should use the `[param]` naming convention 
5. Loading states should use `loading.tsx`
6. Error states should use `error.tsx`
7. API routes should be in the `src/app/api` directory
